# DIG Browser live-path + UX: route dig:// through the local dig-node, render as DIG.
#
# This patch captures the browser changes that make dig:// load via the in-process
# DigURLLoaderFactory (the live navigation + subresource path) and that give the
# browser its DIG identity:
#
#   * chrome/browser/dig/ — the DigURLLoaderFactory source_set: a browser-process
#     URLLoaderFactory that serves dig:// by POSTing dig.getContent to the local
#     dig-node sidecar (default http://127.0.0.1:9778/, DIG_RPC_ENDPOINT override),
#     verifying the Merkle proof against the chain-anchored root (rootless URNs are
#     resolved via the dig-resolver sidecar) and decrypting client-side;
#   * chrome_content_browser_client.cc — register that factory for dig:// for both
#     navigations and subresources;
#   * theme_service.cc — seed the DIG palette (dark + brand violet #5800D6) on a
#     fresh/default profile so the frame/toolbar read as DIG;
#   * home_button.cc + chrome/app/vector_icons/{BUILD.gn,dig_wallet.icon} — the
#     toolbar (former home) button is the DIG Wallet button: it wears a wallet
#     mark — a wallet pouch with a Chia leaf knocked out of its face (the new
#     kDigWalletIcon monochrome toolbar vector icon, tinted by the theme like
#     every other toolbar button); clicking it opens the built-in DIG Wallet
#     (chia://wallet) in a compact popup;
#   * browser_ui_prefs.cc + profile_impl.cc — show the home button and default the
#     home page to https://dig.net/;
#   * render_thread_impl.cc — register dig:// in the renderer as fetch/wasm-capable
#     so dig:// pages can fetch() subresources and instantiate wasm;
#   * chrome/browser/BUILD.gn — depend on //chrome/browser/dig;
#   * chrome_browser_main.cc — at PostBrowserStart, LoadLibrary("dig_runtime.dll")
#     and call dig_runtime_start(): the DIG node runs NATIVE in-process (no
#     dig-node.exe sidecar). build.py stages the cargo-built DLL beside dig.exe.
#   * chrome_render_frame_observer.cc — at DidClearWindowObject, inject the
#     built-in Chia wallet provider (window.chia, CHIP-0002) into every http/
#     https/dig page; the provider proxies to the in-process wallet over loopback
#     and the wallet enforces a per-origin approval gate. build.py generates the
#     embedded dig_provider_js.inc from dig/provider/dig_provider.js.
#
# Generated by diffing the build tree against pristine 139.0.7258.154
# (chrome_content_browser_client.cc baseline includes windows-fix-building-without-
# safebrowsing.patch, which precedes this patch in the series).
--- a/chrome/browser/themes/theme_service.cc
+++ b/chrome/browser/themes/theme_service.cc
